# RTK Gain Enhancement — "Realization Dashboard"

**Date:** 2026-03-09
**Status:** Approved

## Philosophy

- `rtk discover` = **potential** (what you *could* save)
- `rtk gain` = **realization** (what you *are* saving)

## Changes

| Change | Type | Effort |
|--------|------|--------|
| Add Command Coverage section | New section | Medium |
| Hardcoded command→category registry | New const | Small |
| Aggregate tracking data by category | Query post-processing | Small |
| Bridge tip to `rtk discover` | One-liner | Trivial |

## Output Structure

No changes to existing sections (KPIs, efficiency meter, By Command top-10). One new section added after By Command:

```
Command Coverage (10 / 45 commands used)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Category            Used/Avail   Count    Saved    Avg%   Unused
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Git & VCS             4 / 6       129  586.6K   45.2%   gh, gt
  Build & Compile       2 / 6        12    2.0K   95.7%   tsc, next, lint...
  Test                  1 / 4        11    2.7M   96.2%   vitest, playwright...
  Languages             1 / 5        11    2.7M   96.2%   golangci, ruff...
  Files & Search        2 / 7       153   31.4K   77.9%   ls, grep, diff...
  Analysis & Debug      0 / 7         0       0    —      err, json, deps...
  Package Managers      0 / 4         0       0    —      pnpm, npm, npx...
  Infrastructure        0 / 6         0       0    —      docker, kubectl...
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Total: 10 / 45 used    428    3.4M   99.2%  ██████████

  Tip: Run 'rtk discover' to find missed savings opportunities
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
```

## Architecture

### 1. Command Registry

A `const` array mapping each RTK command name to its category. Same categories as `--help` grouping. ~45 entries. Excludes meta/internal commands (gain, discover, init, verify, hook-rewrite, etc.).

```rust
const COMMAND_REGISTRY: &[(&str, &str)] = &[
    ("git", "Git & VCS"),
    ("gh", "Git & VCS"),
    ("gt", "Git & VCS"),
    ("cargo", "Build & Compile"),
    ("tsc", "Build & Compile"),
    // ...
];
```

### 2. Category Aggregation (Rust-side)

- Reuse existing `get_by_command()` which returns `(base_cmd, count, saved, avg_pct, avg_time)`
- Post-process: extract command name from `base_cmd` (strip `rtk ` prefix), look up category in registry, bucket and sum
- "Used" = distinct commands in tracking data that exist in registry
- "Unused" = registry entries not in tracking data, show up to 3 names with `...` if more

### 3. Display

- New function `print_command_coverage(by_command_data)` in `gain.rs`
- Reuses existing helpers: `format_tokens()`, `colorize_pct_cell()`, `mini_bar()`
- Always shown in default output (no flag needed)

### 4. Discover Bridge

- Always print: `Tip: Run 'rtk discover' to find missed savings opportunities`
- Static text, no dynamic calculation

## Unchanged

- All existing flags (--history, --graph, --quota, --daily, --weekly, --monthly, --all, --format, --failures, --project)
- KPI section, efficiency meter, By Command top-10
- Color coding thresholds (green >=70%, yellow >=40%, red <40%)
- JSON/CSV export (coverage data added to JSON export)

## Not Doing

- No per-category savings thresholds
- No separate `rtk stats` command
- No dynamic recommendations beyond the discover tip
- No test DB isolation fix
